title: 1962 Asian Badminton Championships – Men's team
content: The men's team tournament at the inaugural Asian Badminton Championships, also known as the Tunku Abdul Rahman Cup (Malay: Piala Tunku Abdul Rahman) took place from 21 to 28 April 1962 at Stadium Negara in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. The trophy is named after Tunku Abdul Rahman, the first prime minister of Malaysia. A total of 12 teams competed in this event.[1][2]
